---
/**
 * ai-agents · 0005 · Figure 10 — trace tree: run span → step spans → child
 * LLM/tool spans, with the "each span captures" annotation. Verbatim from the
 * source HTML (figcaption carries the footnote <sup> to source 5).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 620 226"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A trace tree: a run span at the root, with step spans, each containing child spans for LLM calls and tool calls, annotated with tokens, cost, latency, and status"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect
                x="20"
                y="14"
                width="500"
                height="26"
                rx="6"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
            <text x="34" y="31" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >RUN &mdash; trace_id 7f3a · task: "fix login bug" · 6 steps · $0.42 · 38s</text
            >
            <!-- step 1 -->
            <rect x="44" y="50" width="476" height="22" rx="5" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect><text x="56" y="65" font-size="9.5" fill="#111110">Step 1 · think</text>
            <rect x="68" y="78" width="300" height="20" rx="5" fill="#eef3fb" stroke="#1f77d0"
            ></rect><text x="78" y="92" font-size="8.5" fill="#1f77d0"
                >LLM call · 4.2k in / 180 out · $0.014 · 1.3s</text
            >
            <!-- step 2 -->
            <rect x="44" y="104" width="476" height="22" rx="5" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect><text x="56" y="119" font-size="9.5" fill="#111110">Step 2 · act</text>
            <rect x="68" y="132" width="320" height="20" rx="5" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect><text x="78" y="146" font-size="8.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >tool: grep_repo("login") &middot; 0.4s &middot; ok &middot; 3 hits</text
            >
            <!-- step 3 -->
            <rect x="44" y="158" width="476" height="22" rx="5" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect><text x="56" y="173" font-size="9.5" fill="#111110">Step 3 · act</text>
            <rect x="68" y="186" width="320" height="20" rx="5" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect><text x="78" y="200" font-size="8.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >tool: write_file(...) &middot; ERROR: permission denied</text
            >
            <!-- annotation -->
            <rect
                x="404"
                y="78"
                width="200"
                height="128"
                rx="8"
                fill="#fbf7ea"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-dasharray="3 2"></rect>
            <text x="504" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >each span captures</text
            >
            <text x="416" y="118" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">· assembled input (context)</text>
            <text x="416" y="135" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">· output / decision</text>
            <text x="416" y="152" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">· tokens &amp; cost</text>
            <text x="416" y="169" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">· latency &amp; status</text>
            <text x="416" y="186" font-size="8.5" fill="#111110">· agent / session id</text>
            <text
                x="504"
                y="201"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="8"
                font-style="italic"
                fill="#6b675f">= replayable</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        One trace per run, one span per step, child spans per LLM/tool call. The span that captures
        the <em>assembled context</em> is what turns "why did it do that?" from a guess into a replay.<sup
            ><a href="#s5" id="r5">5</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
